highlights.description: KC: LVN: reason for showing up to this conversation
KC: Childhood story about a love for libraries
KC: The growth of this city can't accommodate cars for all of the people coming in
KC: I'm worried about health inequities for women of color
LVN script: great way to introduce a highlight
KC: Story in reaction to Hearth highlight about high-rent apartments
KC: Financial education ought to be about how we are all in this together
KC: LVN: we have to learn to bring voices in and deal with real problems
KC: We need voices from all ages to come together
KC: LVN: I really valued this conversation; gives me hope
KC: LVN: hoping LVN goes out to rural communities

Barbara, an African American woman in Madison, WI reflects on health disparities specifically as it relates to infant mortality rates. She credits the Foundation for Black Women's Wellness with helping to reduce these disparities.
